SUMMARY:Lunch and Learn: Sewing Opportunities in Southern WV
DESCRIPTION:Lunch & Learn: Sewing Opportunities in Southern WV –\nwith Taylor Carnell\, PATTERN Operations Manager and Emily Rouse of Edgington Studio \nDiscover how sewn goods connect people\, places\, and possibilities — and why Southern West Virginia is poised to become a hub for textile innovation. Whether you’re an entrepreneur\, a maker\, or simply curious about where your clothing comes from\, this session will open your eyes to the hidden world of textile manufacturing and the exciting future being built through PATTERN. \nWhy Attend?\nThis isn’t just a talk — it’s a chance to connect with a growing network of makers\, learn about training that could open new doors for your career or business\, and see how you can be part of shaping the future of sewn goods in our region.
URL:https://wvbusinesslink.com/event/lunch-and-learn-sewing-opportunities-in-southern-wv/
LOCATION:Zoom Webinar
CATEGORIES:Business Training,Entrepreneurs,Manufacturing,Networking
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://wvbusinesslink.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/Picture1.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="WV Hive Network":MAILTO:information@wvhive.com
END:VEVENT
